/p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uxoralundra.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xoralundra</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Badass Barbarian Shaman</span><br>  Posts: 1559<br> <font color=#660000>(9/27/02 2:41:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=232.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.alexander.darkwave.org.uk/lobo.jpg height=100 width=75 ></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Shaman Heal</span><hr size=1> It doesn't heal for 100%.<br><br>It heals 75% of your health up to a maximum of 1950 hps, i.e. it's most efficient on any toon with over 2600 hps.<br><br>Heal yourself at 5% health and you'll see what I mean.<br><br>But yeah, it's nice for duoing or groups with no cleric. I even tried a druid/shammy &quot;CH rotation&quot; on a Sev kill yesterday. Worked quite well. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Need more gem slots though. :/ <p><DIV align=center><IMG SRC="http://www.alexander.darkwave.org.uk/xorasig.jpg"></DIV><DIV align=center>"For those about to <A HREF="http://www.eq-stone.com/">rock</a>, we shall loot you" /join Xora</DIV><DIV align=center><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=31509">Oracle</A> | <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=264654">Champion</A></DIV></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/usnackoriffic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Snacko Riffic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fatty</span><br>  Posts: 254<br> <font color=#660000>(9/27/02 8:58:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=232.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> blah..</span><hr size=1> First of all, a 10 second cast heal is not a 'spot heal' =)<br><br>Druids get the same spell we do, same mana cost and casting time but their spell heals for an additional 1000.<br><br>I think it needs its mana or casting time reduced, otherwise it is just a slap in the face to give druids a heal for the exact same cost, but with 33% more benefit. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uxoralundra.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xoralundra</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>The Badass Barbarian Shaman</span><br>  Posts: 1561<br> <font color=#660000>(9/27/02 9:24:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=232.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.alexander.darkwave.org.uk/lobo.jpg height=100 width=75 ></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: blah..</span><hr size=1> Let's face it, shaman usually have better things to do in a group/raid situation anyway. I'm happy enough with it, we now have a decent heal for the melee lot, that's good enough for me. Don't compare it to the druid heal and it doesn't seem so bad. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><DIV align=center><IMG SRC="http://www.alexander.darkwave.org.uk/xorasig.jpg"></DIV><DIV align=center>"For those about to <A HREF="http://www.eq-stone.com/">rock</a>, we shall loot you" /join Xora</DIV><DIV align=center><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=31509">Oracle</A> | <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=264654">Champion</A></DIV></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/usssivex.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sssivex</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Heterolite</span><br>  Posts: 255<br> <font color=#660000>(9/27/02 11:15:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fthecrossroadstavern8833frm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=232.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: blah..</span><hr size=1> Its not really that bad...Looking at the benefits of during a fight where a shaman has plenty to do and the druids are sitting back complaining that they have to wait till the mob is at 50 health before they start blastting...Ok this gives them something to do during that interval time.  They can bridge heal way better then I can ever and fine with me.  I made a shaman to help buff, heal casters and slow mobs.  Those are the encounters that I entertain me the best.<br><br>What chokes my goat is the crap buffs that are coming out for PoP.  +60 Stat buffs...Is VI raising the table on these so that they are going to be effective for those that have over 255 points in these.  Did I miss that post?  And I get to buff for an extra 100 hps oh gee thanks.<br><br>I know that I have seen this rant before, but damn I live for something more then a 3950 DoT.  Its nice really, but good lord are these +60 spells only going to work in PoP?  Then when I zone out to kill some epic mob I revert back to only usin &lt;60 lvl spells.   <p><h6><p align="center"><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=40468>Sssive Omphalonosis</A>  Iksar Oracle <br><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=40448> Juagher</A> Iksar Warlord <br><h6> <p align="center">After this long battle, They pillaged our temples, 